  "Mike Speiser is a managing partner at venture capital firm Sutter Hill Ventures, which he joined in 2008.",
  "Speiser was the initial investor in Snowflake and served as its founding CEO from 2012 to 2014.",
  "He became a billionaire after the company went public in September 2020 in what was the largest ever software IPO.",
  "He has a 2% stake in Snowflake's stock.",
  "His other investments include startups Lacework, Sila Nanotechnologies, Clumio, Ghost and Sigma Computing."
